    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> One thing I couldn't find is where we configure conventional-changelog to add algolia/instantsearch.js URLs, because that still seems to be the case recently?\r\n\r\n~~This is probably computed from the remote url set when cloning the repository. When preparing releases locally, this can be solved by recloning from `git@github.com:algolia/instantsearch` (or just updating the remote url), but for scheduled releases I'm not sure where to specify this in CircleCI. I'll check it out.~~\r\n\r\nThis could be incorrect. Circle CI / Shipjs [does set the correct remote url](https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/algolia/instantsearch/9316/workflows/043a16f4-b045-4ab1-9b39-60c1c0038ea7/jobs/45280?invite=true#step-105-6524_83), but because changelogs are generated before, it might be something else that causes the issue.",
